{{italic title}} '''''Dangerous Company: The Consulting Powerhouses and the Businesses They Save and Ruin''''' is a book written by [[James O'Shea (newspaper editor)|James O'Shea]] and [[Charles Madigan]]. It is one of several business books critical of the functioning and importance of the [[Management Consulting|management consulting]] ([[Strategy Consulting]]) industry. The book discusses a range of representative cases and their handling by the top [[Consultant|consulting]] powerhouses.
It was first published in 1997 by [[Times Business]] (New York) as a 355-page hardcover ({{ISBN|0-8129-2634-X}}). [[Penguin Books]] published it as a paperback in 1998 ({{ISBN|0-14-027685-8}}).
